# Reactor-netty, in spring-boot-starter-webflux, there is currently not a fix for it, also does not affect us as it is
# A vulnerability that only affects windows machines.
CVE-2024-47535

# spring-boot-starter-actuator: Authentication bypass only affects CloudFoundry
# endpoints. This application is not deployed on CloudFoundry (no CF profile).
# Fix requires Spring Boot 3.5.12+ — revisit when Spring Boot is upgraded.
CVE-2026-22733

# Trivy false positive: @types/lodash@4.17.24 (type definitions only) is misidentified
# as lodash@4.17.24. The actual lodash runtime is at 4.18.1 which is past the fix threshold.
# No @types/lodash@4.18.x release exists yet to resolve the version mismatch.
CVE-2026-4800

# Spring Security: fix requires Spring Security 6.5.9 which ships with Spring Boot 3.5.x.
# Current Spring Boot is 3.3.x (Spring Security 6.3.x). Revisit when upgrading to Spring Boot 3.5.x.
CVE-2026-22732

# Spring Core: fix requires Spring 6.2.11 which ships with Spring Boot 3.4.x+.
# Current Spring Boot is 3.3.x (Spring 6.1.x). Revisit when upgrading to Spring Boot 3.4.x+.
CVE-2025-41249

# vite is a devDependency (build-time only). The shipped artifact is the built static
# bundle served by nginx/Spring — the vite dev server is never run in CI or prod.
# CVE-2026-53571 is a `server.fs.deny` bypass affecting the dev server on Windows only,
# so it is not applicable (Linux build, no dev server in prod). Revisit by bumping vite to
# 6.4.3+ / 7.x (a major upgrade needing config/plugin review).
CVE-2026-53571